Package org.jsonschema2pojo

Interface GenerationConfig

All Known Implementing Classes:
Arguments, DefaultGenerationConfig, Jsonschema2PojoMojo
public interface GenerationConfig
Defines the configuration options for Java type generation, including source and target paths/packages and all behavioural options (e.g should builders be generated, should primitives be used, etc).

Devs: add to this interface if you need to introduce a new config property.

  • Method Details

    • isGenerateBuilders

      boolean isGenerateBuilders()
      Gets the 'generateBuilders' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to generate builder-style methods of the form withXxx(value) (that return this), alongside the standard, void-return setters.

    • isIncludeTypeInfo

      boolean isIncludeTypeInfo()
      Gets the 'includeTypeInfo' configuration option.
      Returns:
      whether to include json type information. Commonly used to support polymorphic type deserialization.
      See Also:
      • Jackson Polymorphic Deserialization

    • isIncludeConstructorPropertiesAnnotation

      boolean isIncludeConstructorPropertiesAnnotation()
      Gets the 'includeConstructorPropertiesAnnotation' configuration option.
      Returns:
      whether to include JDK Constructor Properties. Used by serialization libraries to get parameter names of constructors at runtime. (Not Available on Android)
      See Also:
      • ConstructorProperties

    • isUsePrimitives

      boolean isUsePrimitives()
      Gets the 'usePrimitives' configuration option.
      Returns:
      whether to use primitives (long, double , boolean) instead of wrapper types where possible when generating bean properties (has the side-effect of making those properties non-null).

    • getSource

      Iterator<URL> getSource()
      Gets the 'source' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The source file(s) or directory(ies) from which JSON Schema will be read.

    • getTargetDirectory

      File getTargetDirectory()
      Gets the 'targetDirectory' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The target directory into which generated types will be written (may or may not exist before types are written)

    • getTargetPackage

      String getTargetPackage()
      Gets the 'targetPackage' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The java package used for generated types.

    • getPropertyWordDelimiters

      char[] getPropertyWordDelimiters()
      Gets the 'propertyWordDelimiters' configuration option.
      Returns:
      an array of characters that should act as word delimiters when choosing java bean property names.

    • isUseLongIntegers

      boolean isUseLongIntegers()
      Gets the 'useLongIntegers' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use the java type long (or Long) instead of int (or Integer) when representing the JSON Schema type 'integer'.

    • isUseBigIntegers

      boolean isUseBigIntegers()
      Gets the 'useBigIntegers' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use the java type BigInteger instead of int (or Integer) when representing the JSON Schema type 'integer'. Note that this configuration overrides isUseLongIntegers().

    • isUseDoubleNumbers

      boolean isUseDoubleNumbers()
      Gets the 'useDoubleNumbers' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use the java type double (or Double) instead of float (or Float) when representing the JSON Schema type 'number'.

    • isUseBigDecimals

      boolean isUseBigDecimals()
      Gets the 'useBigDecimals' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use the java type BigDecimal instead of float (or Float) when representing the JSON Schema type 'number'. Note that this configuration overrides isUseDoubleNumbers().

    • isIncludeHashcodeAndEquals

      boolean isIncludeHashcodeAndEquals()
      Gets the 'includeHashcodeAndEquals' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use include hashCode and equals methods in generated Java types.

    • isIncludeToString

      boolean isIncludeToString()
      Gets the 'includeToString' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use include a toString method in generated Java types.

    • getToStringExcludes

      String[] getToStringExcludes()
      Gets the 'toStringExcludes' configuration option.
      Returns:
      An array of strings representing fields that should be excluded from toString methods

    • getAnnotationStyle

      AnnotationStyle getAnnotationStyle()
      Gets the 'annotationStyle' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The style of annotations to use in the generated Java types.

      Supported values:

      • jackson (alias for jackson2)
      • jackson2 (apply annotations from the Jackson 2.x library)
      • jackson3 (apply annotations from the Jackson 3.x library)
      • gson (apply annotations from the gson library)
      • moshi1 (apply annotations from the moshi library)
      • none (apply no annotations at all)
      See Also:
      • AnnotatorFactory

    • isUseTitleAsClassname

      boolean isUseTitleAsClassname()
      Gets the 'useTitleAsClassname' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use the 'title' property value as the class name for object schemas.

    • getInclusionLevel

      InclusionLevel getInclusionLevel()
      Gets the 'inclusionLevel' option for Jackson serializer.
      Returns:
      Level of inclusion to set in the generated Java types.

      Supported values

      • ALWAYS
      • NON_ABSENT
      • NON_DEFAULT
      • NON_EMPTY
      • NON_NULL
      • USE_DEFAULTS
      See Also:
      • InclusionLevel

    • getCustomAnnotator

      Class<? extends Annotator> getCustomAnnotator()
      Gets the 'customAnnotator' configuration option.
      Returns:
      An annotator that will be used in addition to the one chosen by getAnnotationStyle()

    • getCustomRuleFactory

      Class<? extends RuleFactory> getCustomRuleFactory()
      Gets the 'customRuleFactory' configuration option.
      Returns:
      An Rule Factory that will be used for the creation of generation rules.

    • isIncludeJsr303Annotations

      boolean isIncludeJsr303Annotations()
      Gets the 'includeJsr303Annotations' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to include JSR-303 annotations (for schema rules like minimum, maximum, etc) in generated Java types.

    • isIncludeJsr305Annotations

      boolean isIncludeJsr305Annotations()
      Gets the 'includeJsr305Annotations' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to include JSR-305 annotations (for schema rules like Nullable, NonNull, etc) in generated Java types.

    • isUseOptionalForGetters

      boolean isUseOptionalForGetters()
      Gets the 'useOptionalForGetters' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use Optional as return type for getters of non-required fields.

    • getSourceType

      SourceType getSourceType()
      Gets the 'sourceType' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The type of input documents that will be read

      Supported values:

      • jsonschema
      • json

    • isRemoveOldOutput

      boolean isRemoveOldOutput()
      Gets the 'removeOldOutput' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to empty the target directory before generation occurs, to clear out all source files that have been generated previously. Be warned, when activated this option will cause jsonschema2pojo to indiscriminately delete the entire contents of the target directory (all files and folders) before it begins generating sources.

    • getOutputEncoding

      String getOutputEncoding()
      Gets the 'outputEncoding' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The character encoding that should be used when writing the generated Java source files.

    • isUseJodaDates

      boolean isUseJodaDates()
      Gets the 'useJodaDates' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use DateTime instead of Date when adding date type fields to generated Java types.

    • isUseJodaLocalDates

      boolean isUseJodaLocalDates()
      Gets the 'useJodaLocalDates' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use LocalDate instead of string when adding string type fields with a format of date (not date-time) to generated Java types.

    • isUseJodaLocalTimes

      boolean isUseJodaLocalTimes()
      Gets the 'useJodaLocalTimes' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to use LocalTime instead of string when adding string type fields with a format of time (not date-time) to generated Java types.

    • isParcelable

      boolean isParcelable()
      Gets the 'parcelable' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to make the generated types 'parcelable' (for Android development)

    • isSerializable

      Gets the 'serializable' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to make the generated types 'serializable'

      Gets the 'initializeCollections' configuration option.

      Gets the 'getClassNamePrefix' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to add a prefix to generated classes.

      String getClassNameSuffix()
      Gets the 'getClassNameSuffix' configuration option.

    • getFileExtensions

      String[] getFileExtensions()
      Gets the 'fileExtensions' configuration option.
      Returns:
      An array of strings that should be considered as file extensions and therefore not included in class names.

    • isIncludeConstructors

      boolean isIncludeConstructors()
      Gets the 'includeConstructors' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to generate constructors or not.

    • isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly

      boolean isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly()
      Gets the 'constructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly' configuration option. This is a legacy configuration option used to turn on the isIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor() and off the isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor() configuration options. It is specifically tied to the isIncludeConstructors() property, and will do nothing if that property is not enabled
      Returns:
      whether the resulting object should have a constructor with only the required properties as parameters or all properties.

    • isIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor

      boolean isIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor()
      Gets the 'includeRequiredPropertiesConstructor' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the isIncludeConstructors() configuration option and is incompatible with isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly(), and will have no effect if isIncludeConstructors() is not set to true. .
      Returns:
      whether the resulting object should include a constructor with only the required properties as parameters.

    • isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor

      boolean isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor()
      Gets the 'includeAllPropertiesConstructor' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the isIncludeConstructors() configuration option and is incompatible with isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly(), and will have no effect if isIncludeConstructors() is not set to true.
      Returns:
      whether the resulting object should include a constructor with all listed properties as parameters.

    • isIncludeCopyConstructor

      boolean isIncludeCopyConstructor()
      Gets the 'includeCopyConstructor' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the isIncludeConstructors() configuration option and is incompatible with isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly(), and will have no effect if isIncludeConstructors() is not set to true.
      Returns:
      whether the resulting object should include a constructor the class itself as a parameter, with the expectation that all properties from the originating class will assigned to the new class.

    • isIncludeAdditionalProperties

      boolean isIncludeAdditionalProperties()
      Gets the 'includeAdditionalProperties' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to allow 'additional properties' support in objects. Setting this to false will disable additional properties support, regardless of the input schema(s).

    • isIncludeGetters

      boolean isIncludeGetters()
      Gets the 'includeGetters' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to include getters or to omit these accessor methods and create public fields instead.

    • isIncludeSetters

      boolean isIncludeSetters()
      Gets the 'includeSetters' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to include setters or to omit these accessor methods and create public fields instead.

    • getTargetVersion

      String getTargetVersion()
      Gets the 'targetVersion' configuration option.
      Returns:
      The target version for generated source files.

    • isIncludeDynamicAccessors

      boolean isIncludeDynamicAccessors()
      Gets the `includeDynamicAccessors` configuration option
      Returns:
      Whether to include dynamic getters, setters, and builders or to omit these methods.

      boolean isIncludeDynamicGetters()
      Gets the `includeDynamicGetters` configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to include dynamic getters or to omit these methods

      Gets the `includeDynamicSetters` configuration option.

      Whether to include dynamic setters or to omit these methods

    • isIncludeDynamicBuilders

      boolean isIncludeDynamicBuilders()
      Gets the `includeDynamicBuilders` configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to include dynamic builders or to omit these methods

    • getDateTimeType

      String getDateTimeType()
      Gets the `dateTimeType` configuration option.

      Example values:

      • org.joda.time.LocalDateTime (Joda)
      • java.time.LocalDateTime (JSR310)
      • null (default behavior)
      Returns:
      The java type to use instead of Date when adding date type fields to generate Java types.

    • getDateType

      String getDateType()
      Gets the `dateType` configuration option.

      Example values:

      • org.joda.time.LocalDate (Joda)
      • java.time.LocalDate (JSR310)
      • null (default behavior)
      Returns:
      The java type to use instead of string when adding string type fields with a format of date (not date-time) to generated Java types.

    • getTimeType

      String getTimeType()
      Gets the `timeType` configuration option.

      Example values:

      • org.joda.time.LocalTime (Joda)
      • java.time.LocalTime (JSR310)
      • null (default behavior)
      Returns:
      The java type to use instead of string when adding string type fields with a format of time (not date-time) to generated Java types.

    • isFormatDates

      boolean isFormatDates()
      Gets the `formatDates` configuration option
      Returns:
      Whether the fields of type date have the @JsonFormat annotation with pattern set to the default value of yyyy-MM-dd

    • isFormatTimes

      boolean isFormatTimes()
      Gets the `formatTimes` configuration option
      Returns:
      Whether the fields of type time have the @JsonFormat annotation with pattern set to the default value of HH:mm:ss.SSS

    • isFormatDateTimes

      boolean isFormatDateTimes()
      Gets the `formatDateTime` configuration option
      Returns:
      Whether the fields of type date-type have the @JsonFormat annotation with pattern set to the default value of yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSZ

    • getCustomDatePattern

      String getCustomDatePattern()
      Gets the 'customDatePattern' configuration option
      Returns:
      The custom format that dates will use when types are serialized. Requires support from your JSON binding library.

    • getCustomTimePattern

      String getCustomTimePattern()
      Gets the 'customTimePattern' configuration option
      Returns:
      The custom format that times will use when types are serialized. Requires support from your JSON binding library.

    • getCustomDateTimePattern

      String getCustomDateTimePattern()
      Gets the 'customDateTimePattern' configuration option
      Returns:
      The custom format that dates will use when types are serialized. Requires support from your JSON binding library.

    • getRefFragmentPathDelimiters

      String getRefFragmentPathDelimiters()
      Gets the `refFragmentPathDelimiters` configuration option.
      Returns:
      A string containing any characters that should act as path delimiters when resolving $ref fragments. By default, #, / and . are used in an attempt to support JSON Pointer and JSON Path.

    • getSourceSortOrder

      SourceSortOrder getSourceSortOrder()
      Gets the 'sourceSortOrder' configuration option.
      Returns:

      Supported values:

      • OS (Let the OS influence the order the source files are processed.)
      • FILES_FIRST (Case sensitive sort, visit the files first. The source files are processed in a breadth first sort order.)
      • SUBDIRS_FIRST (Case sensitive sort, visit the sub-directories before the files. The source files are processed in a depth first sort order.)

    • getFormatTypeMapping

      Map<String,String> getFormatTypeMapping()
      Gets the 'formatTypeMapping' configuration option.
      Returns:
      An optional mapping from format identifier (e.g. 'uri') to fully qualified type name (e.g. 'java.net.URI').

    • isUseInnerClassBuilders

      default boolean isUseInnerClassBuilders()
      If set to true, then the gang of four builder pattern will be used to generate builders on generated classes. Note: This property works in collaboration with the isGenerateBuilders() method. If the isGenerateBuilders() is false, then this property will not do anything.
      Returns:
      whether to include the gang of four builder patter on the generated classes. The default value for this is false.

    • isIncludeGeneratedAnnotation

      boolean isIncludeGeneratedAnnotation()
      Gets the 'includeGeneratedAnnotation' configuration option.
      Returns:
      Whether to mark generated classes with the annotation javax.annotation.@Generated (javax.annotation.processing.Generated for Java 9 and later).

    • isUseJakartaValidation

      boolean isUseJakartaValidation()
      Gets the 'useJakartaValidation' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the isIncludeJsr303Annotations() configuration option. If the isIncludeJsr303Annotations() returns false, then this configuration option will not affect anything.
      Returns:
      Whether to use JSR-303 annotations from jakarta.validation package instead of javax.validation package when adding JSR-303 annotations to generated Java types
